2 pounds pork (shoulder) OR 2 pounds beef (strip steak)
3/4 cup brown sugar
1 1/2 Tablespoons salt
3 finely minced cloves garlic 
1 Tablespoon soy sauce
2 Tablespoons rice vinegar
1/2 cup pineapple juice
1/2 Tablespoons fresh ground black pepper
2 Tablespoons Grenadine

-- Steps
1) Slice meat 1/4 inch thick, set aside 
2) Mix all ingrediants in a bowl
3) Add meat to bowl, mix with hand for 30mins to an hour 
4) Put in a sealed container and store in the refridgerator for 3 days
5) If not used in 3 days move container to the freezer. 

-- Cooking 
1) Add 1/2 cup of water to a skillet and add the meat to the skillet
2) Cook until all water is evaporated and the meat is Caramelized 


Server with Garlic fried rice and enjoy :)
